Job scope:
- Assisting in full spectrum HR operation and administration
- Maintain, upkeep and ensure timely and accurate update of HR database, all employee personal files records are complete and treated in strictest confidence
- Application, renewal and cancellation of foreign worker passes
- General HR administration, such as preparation of appointment letters, confirmation letter and etc
- Preparing of new join staffs orientation kit such as sitting arrangement, IT/email setup, stationery, mobile phone, name card, laptop
- Prepare, collate, compile and submit reports for payroll processing
- To assist Procurement when Procurement on leave
- Perform other responsibilities and tasks as assigned

Working Hour: Monday - Thursday 8.30am to 6.30pm, Friday 8.30 - 5.30

Requirement:

  Candidate must possess at least Diploma/Advanced/Higher/Graduate Diploma in Human Resource Management or equivalent.
  At least 1 Year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position
  Required Skill(s): HR, Microsoft Office, Payroll
  Preferably Junior Executive specialized in Human Resources or equivalent
  Immediate vancany will be a plus
